#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an6.112"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an6.112:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 6 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 6 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.112:0.2"
msgid "11. Tikavagga "
msgstr "11. Triads "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an6.112:0.3"
msgid "112. Assādasutta "
msgstr "112. Gratification "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an6.112:1.1"
msgid "“Tayome, bhikkhave, dhammā. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these three things. "

msgctxt "an6.112:1.2"
msgid "Katame tayo? "
msgstr "What three? "

msgctxt "an6.112:1.3"
msgid "Assādadiṭṭhi, attānudiṭṭhi, micchādiṭṭhi. "
msgstr "The view that things are gratifying, the view of self, and wrong view. "

msgctxt "an6.112:1.4"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, tayo dhammā. "
msgstr "These are the three things. "

msgctxt "an6.112:1.5"
msgid "Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya tayo dhammā bhāvetabbā. "
msgstr "To give up these three things you should develop three things. "

msgctxt "an6.112:1.6"
msgid "Katame tayo? "
msgstr "What three? "

msgctxt "an6.112:1.7"
msgid "Assādadiṭṭhiyā pahānāya aniccasaññā bhāvetabbā, attānudiṭṭhiyā pahānāya anattasaññā bhāvetabbā, micchādiṭṭhiyā pahānāya sammādiṭṭhi bhāvetabbā. "
msgstr "You should develop the perception of impermanence to give up the view that things are gratifying; the perception of not-self to give up the view of self; and right view to give up wrong view. "

msgctxt "an6.112:1.8"
msgid "Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya ime tayo dhammā bhāvetabbā”ti. "
msgstr "These are the three things you should develop to give up those three things.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an6.112:1.9"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
